---
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from './ui/card';
---

<section class="py-24 container mx-auto px-4">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto space-y-16">
        
        {/* Header */}
        <div class="text-center space-y-4">
            <div class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-primary/10 text-primary text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest">
                Traveler's Reference
            </div>
            <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl text-foreground">Riomaggiore at a Glance</h2>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto font-serif italic">
                Essential context, common questions, and key data points for the modern explorer.
            </p>
        </div>

        {/* About Section */}
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-12 items-start py-12 border-t border-border/40">
            <div class="md:col-span-4 space-y-4">
                <h3 class="font-serif text-3xl text-foreground leading-tight">The Essence of Riomaggiore</h3>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground font-serif italic">
                    A historic foundation where the mountains meet the Ligurian Sea.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="md:col-span-8 space-y-12">
                <div class="group">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
                        <span class="font-serif text-6xl text-primary/10 group-hover:text-primary/20 transition-colors leading-none select-none">01</span>
                        <div class="space-y-3">
                            <h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-foreground group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">A Vertical History</h4>
                            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed text-lg">
                                Riomaggiore is a historic coastal village in Liguria, Italy, and the easternmost of the five villages of the Cinque Terre. Founded in the 8th century, it is known for its colorful houses built vertically into steep cliffs, its small harbor, and its deep connection to the Ligurian Sea. Riomaggiore is part of the Cinque Terre National Park and is protected as a UNESCO World Heritage Site.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="group">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
                        <span class="font-serif text-6xl text-primary/10 group-hover:text-primary/20 transition-colors leading-none select-none">02</span>
                        <div class="space-y-3">
                            <h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-foreground group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">A Pedestrian Rhythm</h4>
                            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed text-lg">
                                The village is best explored on foot and is easily accessible by train. There is no sandy beach; swimming takes place from rocks and the harbor, where the sea is often clear and inviting. Riomaggiore is especially appreciated for its sunsets, coastal walks, local cuisine, and relaxed rhythm of life.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        {/* Insider Secrets Section */}
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-12 items-start py-12 border-y border-border/40">
            <div class="md:col-span-4 space-y-4">
                <h3 class="font-serif text-3xl text-foreground leading-tight">Do you know Riomaggiore like Giulia does?</h3>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground font-serif italic">
                    Beyond the postcards, there are stories that only those who live here truly understand.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="md:col-span-8 space-y-12">
                <div class="group">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
                        <span class="font-serif text-6xl text-primary/10 group-hover:text-primary/20 transition-colors leading-none select-none">01</span>
                        <div class="space-y-3">
                            <h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-foreground group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">This village exists because hands never stopped working</h4>
                            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed text-lg italic">
                                "People think these cliffs are wild. They’re not. Every terrace you see was built by someone’s nonno, stone by stone. When I walk here, I don’t see landscape — I see centuries of effort holding the village together."
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="group">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
                        <span class="font-serif text-6xl text-primary/10 group-hover:text-primary/20 transition-colors leading-none select-none">02</span>
                        <div class="space-y-3">
                            <h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-foreground group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">Our wine once traveled farther than most of us ever will</h4>
                            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed text-lg italic">
                                "Sciacchetrà isn’t just a sweet wine. My family says it reached Rome, even the Vatican. When I taste it, I feel how something so small and fragile from here could matter so much elsewhere."
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="group">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
                        <span class="font-serif text-6xl text-primary/10 group-hover:text-primary/20 transition-colors leading-none select-none">03</span>
                        <div class="space-y-3">
                            <h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-foreground group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">The houses huddle because they were once afraid</h4>
                            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed text-lg italic">
                                "Our tall, narrow houses weren’t meant to look charming. They were meant to protect us. Pirates came from the sea, and the village learned to close in on itself. That closeness never left — we still live stacked on top of each other, in every sense."
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="group">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
                        <span class="font-serif text-6xl text-primary/10 group-hover:text-primary/20 transition-colors leading-none select-none">04</span>
                        <div class="space-y-3">
                            <h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-foreground group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">We never needed a beach</h4>
                            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed text-lg italic">
                                "Visitors ask where the beach is. There isn’t one — and there never was. The rocks made landing dangerous, and danger kept us safe. I learned to swim from stone, not sand."
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="group">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
                        <span class="font-serif text-6xl text-primary/10 group-hover:text-primary/20 transition-colors leading-none select-none">05</span>
                        <div class="space-y-3">
                            <h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-foreground group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">The train changed everything — and not always gently</h4>
                            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed text-lg italic">
                                "Before the railway, we belonged more to the sea than to the land. Then the tunnel came, cutting through our mountain. Suddenly, Riomaggiore was no longer hidden. Progress arrived loudly."
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="group">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
                        <span class="font-serif text-6xl text-primary/10 group-hover:text-primary/20 transition-colors leading-none select-none">06</span>
                        <div class="space-y-3">
                            <h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-foreground group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">The most romantic path was never meant to be</h4>
                            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed text-lg italic">
                                "Via dell’Amore? It was an accident. A service path for railway workers. We used it because it was there — later, outsiders gave it a name. Romance came after practicality, not before."
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="group">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
                        <span class="font-serif text-6xl text-primary/10 group-hover:text-primary/20 transition-colors leading-none select-none">07</span>
                        <div class="space-y-3">
                            <h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-foreground group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">Fishing was never the whole story</h4>
                            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed text-lg italic">
                                "People imagine fishermen. But most families, including mine, lived from the vineyards. Fishing helped, yes — but the land fed us first. The sea was a partner, not a promise."
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="group">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
                        <span class="font-serif text-6xl text-primary/10 group-hover:text-primary/20 transition-colors leading-none select-none">08</span>
                        <div class="space-y-3">
                            <h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-foreground group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">The colors are for finding home</h4>
                            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed text-lg italic">
                                "Our houses aren’t colorful for postcards. They’re painted so you can recognize your own from the water. When fog rolls in, color is memory."
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="group">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
                        <span class="font-serif text-6xl text-primary/10 group-hover:text-primary/20 transition-colors leading-none select-none">09</span>
                        <div class="space-y-3">
                            <h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-foreground group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">We still walk uphill for protection</h4>
                            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed text-lg italic">
                                "Above the village is Montenero. When things go wrong, people still walk up there — sometimes barefoot, sometimes silently. Faith here isn’t loud. It’s persistent."
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="group">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
                        <span class="font-serif text-6xl text-primary/10 group-hover:text-primary/20 transition-colors leading-none select-none">10</span>
                        <div class="space-y-3">
                            <h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-foreground group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">Riomaggiore is fuller in summer — emptier in winter</h4>
                            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed text-lg italic">
                                "Most houses are closed now. Lights go out early. But winter is when I recognize who truly belongs. Silence reveals us."
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="border-border/40" />

        {/* FAQ Section */}
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-12 items-start py-12">
            <div class="md:col-span-4 space-y-4">
                <h3 class="font-serif text-3xl text-foreground leading-tight">Frequently Asked Questions</h3>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground font-serif italic">
                    Essential information for planning your journey to Riomaggiore.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="md:col-span-8 space-y-12">
                <div class="group">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
                        <span class="font-serif text-6xl text-primary/10 group-hover:text-primary/20 transition-colors leading-none select-none">01</span>
                        <div class="space-y-3">
                            <h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-foreground group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">Where is Riomaggiore located?</h4>
                            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed text-lg">
                                Riomaggiore is located on the Ligurian coast in northern Italy and is one of the five villages of the Cinque Terre, between Manarola and La Spezia.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="group">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
                        <span class="font-serif text-6xl text-primary/10 group-hover:text-primary/20 transition-colors leading-none select-none">02</span>
                        <div class="space-y-3">
                            <h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-foreground group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">Is Riomaggiore worth visiting?</h4>
                            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed text-lg">
                                Yes. Riomaggiore is known for its dramatic setting, authentic atmosphere, and strong connection to the sea. Travelers value it for its views, slower pace, and timeless village character.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="group">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
                        <span class="font-serif text-6xl text-primary/10 group-hover:text-primary/20 transition-colors leading-none select-none">03</span>
                        <div class="space-y-3">
                            <h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-foreground group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">Does Riomaggiore have a beach?</h4>
                            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed text-lg">
                                Riomaggiore does not have a sandy beach. Swimming is done from rocks and the harbor, offering direct access to deep, clear sea water.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="group">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
                        <span class="font-serif text-6xl text-primary/10 group-hover:text-primary/20 transition-colors leading-none select-none">04</span>
                        <div class="space-y-3">
                            <h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-foreground group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">What is the best time to visit?</h4>
                            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed text-lg">
                                Spring and early autumn are ideal for visiting Riomaggiore, offering pleasant temperatures, fewer crowds, and excellent conditions for walking and swimming.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="group">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
                        <span class="font-serif text-6xl text-primary/10 group-hover:text-primary/20 transition-colors leading-none select-none">05</span>
                        <div class="space-y-3">
                            <h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-foreground group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">How do you get to Riomaggiore?</h4>
                            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed text-lg">
                                Riomaggiore is best reached by train via the Cinque Terre railway line. Cars are not allowed inside the village, making it a pedestrian-friendly destination.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="group">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
                        <span class="font-serif text-6xl text-primary/10 group-hover:text-primary/20 transition-colors leading-none select-none">06</span>
                        <div class="space-y-3">
                            <h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-foreground group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">How long should you stay?</h4>
                            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed text-lg">
                                Many travelers visit for a day, but staying one or two nights allows you to experience quieter mornings and evenings, which are often the most memorable moments.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="group">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
                        <span class="font-serif text-6xl text-primary/10 group-hover:text-primary/20 transition-colors leading-none select-none">07</span>
                        <div class="space-y-3">
                            <h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-foreground group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">Is Riomaggiore crowded?</h4>
                            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed text-lg">
                                Riomaggiore can be busy during peak hours in summer. Early mornings and evenings are generally calmer and more enjoyable.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="group">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
                        <span class="font-serif text-6xl text-primary/10 group-hover:text-primary/20 transition-colors leading-none select-none">08</span>
                        <div class="space-y-3">
                            <h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-foreground group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">What is Riomaggiore known for?</h4>
                            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed text-lg">
                                Riomaggiore is known for its colorful cliffside houses, small harbor, sunsets over the Ligurian Sea, local wine, and its authentic Cinque Terre atmosphere.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>
</section>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "TouristDestination",
  "name": "Riomaggiore",
  "description": "Riomaggiore is a historic coastal village in Liguria, Italy, and the easternmost of the five villages of the Cinque Terre.",
  "address": {
    "@type": "PostalAddress",
    "addressLocality": "Riomaggiore",
    "addressRegion": "Liguria",
    "addressCountry": "Italy"
  },
  "geo": {
    "@type": "GeoCoordinates",
    "latitude": 44.0985,
    "longitude": 9.7386
  },
  "touristType": [
    "HistoricSite",
    "NatureReserve"
  ],
  "publicAccess": true,
  "isAccessibleForFree": true
}
</script>
